# Narnach's Loot filter for Leveling
#
# This filter shows items that are appropriate for the area where they drop, and as such contains a lot of rules to cover the leveling curve. While leveling this is great, but once you hit maps I encourage you to switch to the Maps or Maps-Strict versions of this filter.
#
# Changelog:
# - 27 August 2017: Don't show red font for 5-link
# - 26 August 2017: Highlight Divine Vessel
# - 12 August 2017: Harbinger Shards have varying highlights
# - 7 August 2017: Harbinger League Updates, positional custom orb sounds
# - 18 July 2017: Show 4-socketed items until maps, instead of until level 40.
# - 18 July 2017: Shuffled currency tiers around and changed their look to stand out a bit less.
# - 16 July 2017: Show all 4-links until level 40 (up from 35). Makes gearing in Dried Lake easier.
# - 4 July 2017: Remove 3.0 gem highlights, make regular gems more visible
# - 10 June 2017: Highlight new 3.0 gems
# - 28 April 2017: Show rares when mapping (Orbs of Alteration are obtained from selling rares)
# - 2 April 2017: Highlight Orb of Augmentation
# - 1 April 2017: Currencies of different tiers get different sounds and colours.
# - 1 April 2017: Highlight quality flasks + 20% quality items. Removed border from low level jewelry.
# - 19 March 2017: Remove chaos/regal rare highlights, show all endgame base items when normal/rare
# - 5 March 2017: Hide rare items that are more than 10-15 levels below you. Legacy League spams rares!
# - 5 March 2017: Talismans are larger so they are easier to pickup in combat.
# - 4 March 2017: Make scrolls stand out a bit more - initial tuning was for maps, not leveling
# - 3 March 2017: Added Legacy League support & added more sounds to important drops
#
# Author: wes@narnach.com
#         https://www.youtube.com/narnach
#         https://www.twitter.com/narnach
#         http://www.twitch.tv/narnach
#         https://gist.github.com/Narnach/79e57e9846851e69eb01
#
# This is the Path of Exile loot filter I use in my recordings.
# It keeps evolving over time, as my needs keep changing.
#
# My biases are towards my playstyle and my needs. Yours may be different.
#
# These item types have their own leveling curve, so you only see the "current" version of them.
# The only reason they are in here is because I played a build that used them, and thus I spent the hour needed to map it out.
# Other item types follow a general curve where you see them up to 10 levels below the area.
#
# - Sceptres: elemental damage trumps physical damage. It's a caster tool, not a melee weapon.
# - Thrusting Swords
# - 1h Axes
# - Str armour
# - Int armour
# - Armour shields
#
# When making changes, it is very useful to use the wiki page as a reference:
#
#   http://pathofexile.gamepedia.com/Item_filter_guide
#
# A big shout out to Quill18, whose loot filter I used as a sane starting point for my own.
# I've made so many changes that it's very different now, but credit is due anyway.
# If you think my filter has too many colors, Quill18's filter is simpler.
#
# Quill18's Simple LootFilter
#   Author: quill18@quill18.com
#           youtube.com/quill18
#           https://gist.github.com/quill18/d811f616d577bed035b4
#
#  **Installation**
#
#  Copy to:  C:\Users\<USERNAME>\Documents\My Games\Path of Exile\
#     NOTE:  The file MUST have the ".filter" extension.
#
#  In Path of Exile, go to Options -> UI -> <Scroll down to the bottom> ->
#       Select the filter from the pulldown -> Click "Reload".
#

